The paper proposes a new unsupervised approach based on deep learning for time series segmentation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with data sequences and statistical methods, which may make it relevant to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with electroencephalogram (EEG) activity traces, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
